{{primary sources|date=September 2011}} {{refimprove|date=April 2009}} {{Infobox Software | name = CDBurnerXP | logo = [[Image:Cdbxpp logo.png|CDBurnerXP Logo]] | screenshot = [[Image:CdburnerXP screenshot.png|200px]] | caption = CDBurnerXP 4 | developer = Canneverbe Limited | released = 2003-02-18 | frequently_updated = yes<!-- Release version update? Don't edit this page, just click on the version number! --> | programming language = VB.NET, C# | operating system = [[Microsoft Windows]] | language = English, Multilingual | genre = [[Optical disc authoring]] | license = [[Freeware]] ([[Closed Source]]) | website = [http://cdburnerxp.se/ cdburnerxp.se] }} '''CDBurnerXP''' is an [[optical disc authoring software]] application for [[Microsoft Windows]], written mostly in [[Visual Basic .NET]] as of version 4, released in September 2007.<ref name="v4_release">{{cite web |url=http://forum.cdburnerxp.se/viewtopic.php?f=2&t=5114 |title=CDBurnerXP 4.0 final released |publisher=CDBurnerXP |date=22 September 2007 |accessdate=25 April 2010}}</ref> It has [[internationalization|international language support]]. The software is available to download in both 32bit and 64bit variants.
The program supports burning data on [[CD-R]], [[CD-RW]], [[DVD-R]], [[DVD-RW]], [[DVD+R]], [[DVD+RW]], [[Blu-ray Disc]] and [[HD DVD]] as well as burning audio files ([[WAV]], [[MP3]], [[MP2]], [[FLAC]], [[Windows Media Audio]], [[AIFF]], [[BWF]] (Broadcast WAV), and [[Ogg Vorbis]]) in the [[Red Book (audio CD standard)|Red Book]] format. [[ISO image]]s can be burnt and created. It can burn [[Universal Disk Format|UDF]] and/or [[ISO-9660]] formats. Bootable data discs are supported as well.
CDBurnerXP is [[freeware]] but [[closed source]] because it currently uses some proprietary libraries<ref>[http://cdburnerxp.se/help/kb:4 CDBurnerXP: KB4: CDBurnerXP and Open Source<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>. The standard CDBurnerXP installer comes bundled with [[OpenCandy]], though a version without this is available, alongside an MSI for corporate deloyment and a portable version requiring no installation<ref>[http://cdburnerxp.se/en/download CDBurnerXP Download Page (click "More download options" to see other choices]</ref>.
